The paper deals with the performance analysis of linear MIMO receivers in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, based on the abstract and the keywords provided, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems and the design of efficient coding and modulation schemes. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.COM (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which are all relevant to the analysis and optimization of wireless communication systems.
